Manufacturing Technician job
in Singapore
Job Ref:
15958BR
COUNTRY:
Singapore
CITY:
Singapore
EMPLOYER:
INDUSTRY:
Manufacturing/Production
Why Thermo Fisher Scientific? We are a $17 billion company with over 50,000 employees worldwide and we look after our staff. On top of attractive bonus payouts, industry standard overtime payments and a unique 'no shift work' practice, we have a variety of staff benefits that will cover you and your immediate family. If you are looking to be part of an organization that champions progress and growth while making the world a healthier, cleaner and safer place, look no further. Responsibilities
Assembling, testing, troubleshooting of products and training of other Specialists / Operators, Manufacturing to ensure that standard and specifications are met. Assembly and testing of the product to ensure that all required specifications are met.
Work with Executive, Manufacturing and Engineers to ensure that quality, waste and efficiency are meeting the requirements. Troubleshoot faulty product or parts to ensure that all required specifications are met. Execute improvement activities on quality and work process efficiency Maintain ISO9001, ISO14001, ISO13485, QSR21CFR and OHSAS 18001 documentations to ensure conformity. Maintain and upkeep the housekeeping and safety standards in the workplace. Minimum Qualifications (must have) Requirements NTC 3 in technical discipline. NTC2 in technical discipline. Understand ISO requirements*LI-NG1Preferred Qualifications (nice to have) NA EOE
Post Date:
05/03/2014
